Key Match Events: The Detroit Pistons defeated the Toronto Raptors 99-95.
Six different Pistons players finished in double figures.
Wendell Moore Jr. and Marcus Sasser made significant contributions in the fourth quarter.
Moore made key rebounds and transition buckets, limiting Raptors' forward Gradey Dick to a tough shooting night.
Sasser hit two big triples and made a crucial steal against Gradey Dick in the fourth quarter.
Cade Cunningham recorded his sixth double double of the season with 15 points, 10 assists, and six rebounds.
Post-Match Reflections: Cade Cunningham praised Wendell Moore Jr. and Marcus Sasser for their energy and contributions.
Cunningham expressed happiness for rookie Ron Holland II, who finished with ten points, eight rebounds, and three steals.
Cunningham reflected on Holland's mental strength and his ability to overcome tough plays.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Jaden Ivey returned from injury and contributed 14 points in 28 minutes.
Veteran shooter Malik Beasley led the Pistons in scoring with 20 points on 8-15 shooting.
